info.description: # FactSet Tick History client library for Python [![PyPi](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/fds.sdk.FactSetTickHistory)](https://pypi.org/project/fds.sdk.FactSetTickHistory/) [![Apache-2 license](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache2-brightgreen.svg)](https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0) TickHistory provides dynamic access to historical tick data for a specific security for specific dates or date range. This parameter is used to identify the beginning of next set of results (optional) (default to 0) try: # Returns the files from tickhistory endpoint for the specified date range api_response = api_instance.v1_get_files_get(request_id, pagination_limit=pagination_limit, pagination_offset=pagination_offset) pprint(api_response) except fds.sdk.FactSetTickHistory.ApiException as e: print("Exception when calling GetFilesApi->v1_get_files_get: %s\n" % e) ``` ## Documentation for API Endpoints All URIs are relative to *https://api-sandbox.factset.com/bulk-documents/tickhistory* Class | Method | HTTP request | Description ------------ | ------------- | ------------- | ------------- *GetFilesApi* | [**v1_get_files_get**](docs/GetFilesApi.md#v1_get_files_get) | **GET** /v1/get-files | Returns the files from tickhistory endpoint for the specified date range *RequestFilesApi* | [**v1_request_files_get**](docs/RequestFilesApi.md#v1_request_files_get) | **GET** /v1/request-files | Returns the requestId and status ## Documentation For Models - [Data](docs/Data.md) - [GetFilesErrorDetail](docs/GetFilesErrorDetail.md) - [GetFilesResponse](docs/GetFilesResponse.md) - [GetFilesStatus](docs/GetFilesStatus.md) - [Meta](docs/Meta.md) - [Pagination](docs/Pagination.md) - [Partial](docs/Partial.md) - [RequestFileErrorDetails](docs/RequestFileErrorDetails.md) - [RequestFilesResponse](docs/RequestFilesResponse.md) - [RequestFilestatus](docs/RequestFilestatus.md) ## Documentation For Authorization ## FactSetApiKey - **Type**: HTTP basic authentication ## FactSetOAuth2 - **Type**: OAuth - **Flow**: application - **Authorization URL**: - **Scopes**: N/A ## Notes for Large OpenAPI documents If the OpenAPI document is large, imports in fds.sdk.FactSetTickHistory.apis and fds.sdk.FactSetTickHistory.models may fail with a RecursionError indicating the maximum recursion limit has been exceeded.
